					<head>Sefer mitsṿot gadol</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287" rend="visible">
						<summary>The second part of the Sefer mitsṿot gadol of Moses ben Jacob of Coucy.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287">
							<locus from="1r" to="414v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sefer mitsṿot gadol</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">ספר מצות גדול</title>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/88359425">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/88359425" xml:lang="en">Moses ben Jacob, of Coucy, active 13th century</persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/88359425" xml:lang="he">משה בן יעקב, מקוצי</persName>
							</author>
							<listBibl>
								<bibl>
									<ref target="Sefer_mitsvot_gadol_1488"/>
								</bibl>
							</listBibl>
							<note>
								<p>A fragment of a list of mitsṿot lo taʿaseh (nos. 145-365) is prefixed, folios 1r-8v.</p>
								<p>The text differs in some parts from the printed editions.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 14th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment codex.</support>
								<extent>414 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>210</height>
										<width>185</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p> 414 folios (+ 4 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and 3 at the end). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>52 quires of mostly 8 leaves each. Imperfect at the beginning and at the end. Lacuna after folio 412.</p>
									<p>Quires marked with Hebrew letters and Roman figures in reverse order at the end.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Defective at the beginning and at the end. </p>
									<p>Lacuna of 12 leaves after folio 412.</p>
									<p>Folio 412 much mutilated.</p>
									<p>Slightly stained.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="25" writtenLines="25">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Pricking and ruling with hard point visible. </p>
									<p>Flesh side and hair side distinguishable.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Oriental semi-cursive script, unpunctuated, of 14th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major">
								<p/>
							</handNote>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Folio 1 contains a fragment on עריות belonging to another Sefer mitsṿot.</p>
							<p>A fragment of the list of mitsṿot lo taʿaseh is prefixed.</p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>BM/BL in-house.</p>
								<p>Spine title: 'Moses of Coucy. Sepher Mitsvoth Gadol. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Additional 27, 040.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
					</physDesc>
